{"cursor":"3267","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Magazine\n  | title = Signs of the Times image_file = image_size = image_caption = editor\n  | = Marvin Moore editor_title = Editor frequency = monthly paid_circulation =\n  | unpaid_circulation = total_circulation = category = Christian - Seventh-day\n  | Adventist company = publisher = Pacific Press firstdate = June 4, 1874\n  | country = language = English website = [http://www.signstimes.com\n  | www.signstimes.com] issn = 0037-5047\n}}\n\n\n'Signs of the Times' is a monthly magazine published by Pacific Press, a Seventh-\nday Adventist publishing house. Signs presents articles that are helpful in\nassisting Christian readers to live in modern society. The magazine emphasizes\nthe second coming of Christ to this earth.\n\nSigns of the Times' library reference number is .\n\nSigns is also available as a completely separate Australian version also known\nas [[Signs of the Times (Australia)|Signs of the Times]] published by Signs\nPublishing Company. The Australian editor is Lee Dunstan.\n\nIn South Africa the Southern Publishing Association published a South African\nedition until 1990. From 1990 - 2012, Dr Eric Webster served as manager/editor\nof \"Signs\", publishing the magazine on behalf of the Southern African Union\nConference of Seventh-day Adventists (SAU). Webster retired at the end of\n2012. Dr Gerald du Preez now serves as editor, with the management and\npublishing of \"Signs\", South African edition, directly under the Communication\nDepartment of the SAU.\n","linknr":176,"url":"Signs_of_the_Times_(magazine)","recorded":1363470338,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Signs_of_the_Times_(magazine)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Signs_of_the_Times_(magazine)&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?